1. Always assume nobody can see you.
2. Ride in the left hand lane whenever possible.
  a. This puts you on the drivers side of the vehicle
  b. You will have one less side to watch for vehicles on
3. Avoid riding next to vehicles.
4. Never ride on the right hand side of a big truck.
5. Protect your lane by riding in the right hand track
   a. But move more centered when coming to an intersection where people will be making left hand turns to be more visible.
6. Remember regardless of who is at fault for an accident you will be the one that will suffer the most damage to your body.
